        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 3:15PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 314 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Gum Creek, or near
Covington, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Walnut Grove, Herndonville, Between, Gum Creek, Monroe, Youth,
Jersey, Pannell, Oxford, Good Hope, Loganville, and Conyers.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
